3. Forecast the Best Model

4. Analyze the Forecast Error of the Best Model

Employment inverse-difference forecast error doesn’t pass the ADF test nor the Ljung-Box test up to 24 lags when critical value=5%. The correlogram suggests an AR(1) effect.

CPI inverse-difference forecast error doesn’t pass the ADF test nor the Ljung-Box test to 24 lags when critical value=5%. The correlogram suggests an AR(1) effect.


Since the best model is selected based on the lowest RMSEs’ sum, employment’s much larger scale overweights employment’s RMSE. So in this best model, employment forecast is much better than CPI forecast. If we use percentage error, both errors can have equal weights.
